=== Main festivals ===
* Summer Festival ({{ill|lt=August 1st|Q2788|WD=Q2788|1=August 1}}-{{ill|lt=August 2nd|Q2785|WD=Q2785|lt=2nd|1=August 2}})
*: Also called the ``Goshinko Festival,'' {{ill|lt=Mikoshi|Q979940|WD=Q979940|1=Mikoshi}} is paraded around Tsuno Town. It is said that the name comes from the fact that Empress Jingu brought the enshrined deity of the company to her boat as a guardian deity during the Sanhan Conquest, and there was a time when it was discontinued, but it was revived in {{ill|lt=Tenpo|Q1369045|WD=Q1369045|1=Tenpō}}3 ({{ill|lt=1832|Q7584|WD=Q7584|1=1832}}).
* Winter Festival ({{ill|lt=December 4th|Q2310|WD=Q2310|1=December 4}}-{{ill|lt=December 5th|Q2300|WD=Q2300|lt=5th|1=December 5}})
*: Kagura is played throughout the night, and the annual festival is held on the 5th. Also, on that day, it is said that if a woman suffering from breast ailments offers a ladle, she will be cured.

